# Phase 3.5: Clean Architecture Consolidation Plan

This phase consolidates the backend codebase by swapping live traffic to the newly created clean architecture modules, cleaning up runtime service dependencies (Telegram Bot and Sockets), and deleting obsolete legacy controllers, routes, and services.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Complete Legacy Deletion**: This plan deletes **13 obsolete legacy files** (5 routes, 6 controllers, and 2 services) that are now fully migrated to the Clean Architecture modules.
> **Zero Production Logic Modifications**: This phase does not introduce new features or change state machine transitions; it is strictly a structural routing and dependency consolidation phase.

