## Migration Order

1. **Step 1**: Refactor [telegramService.js](file:///c:/Users/bibha/Desktop/sahayog-sarthi/backend/src/services/telegramService.js) and [socketService.js](file:///c:/Users/bibha/Desktop/sahayog-sarthi/backend/src/services/socketService.js) to consume use cases dynamically.
2. **Step 2**: Update [bookingRoutes.js](file:///c:/Users/bibha/Desktop/sahayog-sarthi/backend/src/modules/booking/interfaces/http/routes/bookingRoutes.js) to import from clean ChatController.
3. **Step 3**: Rewrite route mounts inside [index.js](file:///c:/Users/bibha/Desktop/sahayog-sarthi/backend/src/index.js) to swap routes to clean modules.
4. **Step 4**: Run full backend test suite to check for any local runtime compilation or route registration errors.
5. **Step 5**: Update route/service imports inside test files [bookingStateMachine.test.js](file:///c:/Users/bibha/Desktop/sahayog-sarthi/backend/tests/bookingStateMachine.test.js) and [paymentRedirect.test.js](file:///c:/Users/bibha/Desktop/sahayog-sarthi/backend/tests/paymentRedirect.test.js).
6. **Step 6**: Run automated tests again to confirm 23/23 tests pass cleanly.
7. **Step 7**: Delete all legacy routes, controllers, and services listed in the deletion plan.
8. **Step 8**: Run final verification tests and live server smoke tests.

## Risk Assessment

- **Circular Dependency Crash**: Dynamically importing the booking container inside `telegramService.js` callback execution flow mitigates the circular dependency route during early ES module registration.
- **Test App Route Mismatch**: Solved by updating test router setup to mirror `index.js` route swaps.

## Rollback Strategy
- Discard changes using `git restore .` and restore files from the `phase3-4-stable` tag.

